    "body": "fwiw we use a similar custom genesis and this (in docker, but you can just run it locally):\n\nENTRYPOINT [\"./go-ethereum/build/bin/geth\"]\n\nCMD [\"--networkid\", \"234567\", \"--rpc\", \"--rpcaddr\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--nodiscover\", \"--rpcapi\", \"eth,net,web3,admin,miner,personal\"]\n\nthese days we also:\n\n./go-ethereum/build/bin/geth init ./CustomGenesis.json \n\nbefore running.  \n\nWe're connecting on port 8545.  \n\nWorth noting that our system (which also uses ether pudding) stopped working properly sometime between geth 1.4.3 and 1.4.7 - still trying to figure out why.  We're running a miner and a bunch of non-mining geth clients - you can send txns from the miner to the clients, but the other way around they just get stuck.  1.4.3 is fine.\n\nPing me if this doesn't help.  I can always send you our docker file.  \n",
