    "body": "I'm trying to set up a private geth single node chain and I am encountering the following:\nUsing latest geth (1.4.9) and connecting via [browser-solidity](http://ethereum.github.io/browser-solidity/#version=soljson-latest.js), mined contracts don't appear to be running their constructors, since the 'owner' address is set to '0x0' rather than 'msg.sender'.\nUsing geth 1.4.3 as suggested above results in the solidity browser interface reporting that no code exists at addresses after mining has been done.\n\nEDIT: Ok so it actually does work when I wrote and deployed a simple test contract. My gut feeling is that the imports and dependencies are screwing it up... I will investigate more.\n\nEDIT: The problem shows up when adding a line that creates another contract instance as follows:\n\n```\nimport \"./c2.sol\";\n\ncontract c1 {\n    address public c2;\n\n    function addC2 () {\n        c2 = new c2();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe specificity of this probably now deviates from the original post...\n\nEDIT: After more investigation it appears that the problem is related to the gas cost for the transaction exceeding 1 million.\n",
