    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The RPC endpoint (8545 by default) speaks the JSON RPC protocol. If you just connect to it without sending anything and wait it doesn't know what to do as it itself is waiting for a request to reply to. If you would execute an HTTP `GET` against it (e.g. from a browser window), you get back `{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"error\":{\"code\":-32600,\"message\":\"EOF\"}}` so that seems fine to me.\n\nPort 30303 is the devp2p port that we use for P2P data exchange, to run the Ethereum network. You shouldn't attach to that.\n\nWith regard to transaction propagation, there was an update to fix a sync issue that didin't consider a single miner scenario. It's a pending bug tracked in https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/2769.\n",
